ivor-of-an-ancient-lunar-collision-180988785/</guid></item><item><title>“法国班克斯”​​的最新艺术作品中，巴黎最古老的桥梁一夜之间被巨大的充气洞穴吞没</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-oldest-bridge-in-paris-was-swallowed-overnight-by-a-giant-inflatable-cave-in-latest-artwork-by-the-french-banksy-180988781/</link><description>法国街头艺术家 JR 选择新桥作为他最新的具有传奇色彩的艺术装置的画布，该装置由傻朋克音乐家的音频伴奏创作</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 19:04:20 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-oldest-bridge-in-paris-was-swallowed-overnight-by-a-giant-inflatable-cave-in-latest-artwork-by-the-french-banksy-180988781/</guid></item><item><title>随着《幸存者》第 50 季的结束，史密森学会从这部标志性真人秀节目中获得了备受追捧的免疫项链和其他道具</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/as-survivor-marks-its-50th-season-finale-the-smithsonian-acquires-immunity-necklaces-and-other-props-from-the-iconic-reality-tv-show-180988780/</link><description>热门节目第一季和最近几季的物品将被添加到美国国家历史博物馆的永久收藏中</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 17:38:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/as-survivor-marks-its-50th-season-finale-the-smithsonian-acquires-immunity-necklaces-and-other-props-from-the-iconic-reality-tv-show-180988780/</guid></item><item><title>为什么几乎每个人都是右撇子，但不是每个猿和猴子都是右利手？新研究探索人类惯用手的进化起源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-is-nearly-every-person-right-handed-but-not-every-ape-and-monkey-new-research-explores-the-evolutionary-origins-of-human-handedness-180988776/</link><description>最新研究表明，大脑大小和双足行走是人类右手优势的最有可能的驱动因素</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 16:28:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-is-nearly-every-person-right-handed-but-not-every-ape-and-monkey-new-research-explores-the-evolutionary-origins-of-human-handedness-180988776/</guid></item><item><title>这些纳粹掠夺的杰作的所有者是谁？在法国最受欢迎的博物馆之一展示它们能否帮助追查它们？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/who-are-the-owners-of-these-nazi-looted-masterpiecesand-could-displaying-them-at-one-of-frances-most-popular-museums-help-track-them-down-180988779/</link><description>奥赛博物馆的一个新的永久展览展示了二战期间可能被盗或在可疑情况下被出售的艺术品。官员们仍然希望找到其合法主人的家人</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 15:02:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/who-are-the-owners-of-these-nazi-looted-masterpiecesand-could-displaying-them-at-one-of-frances-most-popular-museums-help-track-them-down-180988779/</guid></item><item><title>突破性的 DNA 分析鉴定出马里兰殖民地最早定居者的 130 万在世亲属</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/groundbreaking-dna-analysis-identifies-13-million-living-relatives-of-colonial-marylands-earliest-settlers-180988778/</link><description>专家将埋在圣玛丽市墓地的 49 具骸骨的 DNA 与 1150 万 23andMe 用户共享的基因数据进行了比较。他们还确定了可能是该殖民地第二任总督的遗骸</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 14:49:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/groundbreaking-dna-analysis-identifies-13-million-living-relatives-of-colonial-marylands-earliest-settlers-180988778/</guid></item><item><title>一项研究表明，地中海僧海豹在繁忙的夏季隐藏在水下“气泡洞”中以避免游客</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mediterranean-monk-seals-hide-in-underwater-bubble-caves-to-avoid-tourists-during-the-busy-summer-season-a-study-suggests-180988775/</link><description>研究人员在希腊福米库拉岛上的一个僻静的房间里发现了这种罕见的鳍足类动物正在休息和睡觉。研究结果表明，这些小洞穴应该被纳入保护动物栖息地的努力中</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 14:40:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mediterranean-monk-seals-hide-in-underwater-bubble-caves-to-avoid-tourists-during-the-busy-summer-season-a-study-suggests-180988775/</guid></item><item><title>加拿大这座矿井每年可能会释放出足够的天然氢来为 400 户家庭供电，这暗示着清洁能源尚未开发的来源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-canadian-mine-might-release-enough-natural-hydrogen-each-year-to-power-400-homes-hinting-at-an-untapped-source-of-clean-energy-180988773/</link><description>该国的许多金属矿山都埋藏在古老的岩层中，该岩层可能还蕴藏着大量被称为“白氢”的资源</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-canadian-mine-might-release-enough-natural-hydrogen-each-year-to-power-400-homes-hinting-at-an-untapped-source-of-clean-energy-180988773/</guid></item><item><title>发现的一批骨头和牙齿为老挝百年之谜“死亡罐子”提供了新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-discovered-trove-of-bones-and-teeth-yields-new-clues-to-the-century-old-mystery-of-death-jars-in-laos-180988772/</link><description>科学家们在东南亚最令人费解的考古遗址之一的一个巨大石罐里发现了 37 具骨头。这一发现表明了多代人的埋葬方式</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 21:08:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-discovered-trove-of-bones-and-teeth-yields-new-clues-to-the-century-old-mystery-of-death-jars-in-laos-180988772/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家从德国的一个中世纪厕所中取出了一本原始的皮革笔记本，其中保存了几个世纪以来的拉丁草书</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/from-a-medieval-latrine-in-germany-archaeologists-extracted-a-pristine-leather-notebook-that-preserved-latin-cursive-for-centuries-180988771/</link><description>小册子上的文字表明它属于一位上层商人，他可能在 800 年前使用厕所时发生了事故</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 19:11:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/from-a-medieval-latrine-in-germany-archaeologists-extracted-a-pristine-leather-notebook-that-preserved-latin-cursive-for-centuries-180988771/</guid></item><item><title>科学家表示，巴布亚企鹅实际上是四种不同的物种，这表明它们毕竟不是气候变化的“赢家”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gentoo-penguins-may-actually-be-four-different-species-scientists-say-revealing-theyre-not-quite-winners-of-climate-change-after-all-180988769/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，随着时间的推移，随着孤立的种群发生变化以适应其环境条件，适应性强的鸟类进化成不同的谱系。这项工作对自然资源保护主义者如何评估巴布亚蜥蜴的威胁具有重要意义</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 19:09:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gentoo-penguins-may-actually-be-four-different-species-scientists-say-revealing-theyre-not-quite-winners-of-climate-change-after-all-180988769/</guid></item><item><title>螃蟹什么时候进化出标志性的侧身飞艇？科学家将其追溯到 2 亿年前的共同祖先</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/when-did-crabs-evolve-their-iconic-sideways-scuttle-scientist-traced-it-to-a-200-million-year-old-common-ancestor-180988765/</link><description>研究结果表明，它们著名的横向运动只进化过一次。它可能帮助动物迅速扩散和多样化，因为向两个方向移动意味着它们可以轻松逃脱捕食者</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 15:57:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/when-did-crabs-evolve-their-iconic-sideways-scuttle-scientist-traced-it-to-a-200-million-year-old-common-ancestor-180988765/</guid></item><item><title>一项新研究表明，定期穿着降温背心可能会帮助您减少体内脂肪</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/regularly-wearing-a-cooling-vest-might-help-you-lose-body-fat-according-to-a-new-study-180988767/</link><description>超重或肥胖的参与者每天早上佩戴这些配件两个小时，持续六周，平均减重两磅。研究人员怀疑在冷水中淋浴或游泳可能会产生类似的效果</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 13:11:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/regularly-wearing-a-cooling-vest-might-help-you-lose-body-fat-according-to-a-new-study-180988767/</guid></item><item><title>这只野狗很可能被袋鼠踢到，但它在千年前就痊愈了，这要归功于 500 年来一直尊重它的原住民社区的帮助</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/likely-kicked-by-a-kangaroo-this-dingo-healed-a-millennium-ago-thanks-to-help-from-an-aboriginal-community-that-continued-to-honor-it-for-500-years-180988768/</link><description>新的研究表明，澳大利亚巴金吉人的祖先在野狗死后的几个世纪里，按照仪式将河蚌贝壳添加到墓地，这表明他们对它非常关心</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 21:06:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/likely-kicked-by-a-kangaroo-this-dingo-healed-a-millennium-ago-thanks-to-help-from-an-aboriginal-community-that-continued-to-honor-it-for-500-years-180988768/</guid></item><item><title>大英博物馆准备将这件杰作平放，贝叶挂毯开启全新视角之旅</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-bayeux-tapestry-takes-a-journey-for-a-fresh-perspective-as-the-british-museum-prepares-to-lay-the-masterpiece-out-flat-180988764/</link><description>在法国度过了几个世纪之后，这幅描绘诺曼征服英格兰的 1000 年历史的挂毯正在回到自己的祖国</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 20:09:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-bayeux-tapestry-takes-a-journey-for-a-fresh-perspective-as-the-british-museum-prepares-to-lay-the-masterpiece-out-flat-180988764/</guid></item><item><title>“反灭绝”公司表示，它用人造鸡蛋孵化出小鸡，为复活渡渡鸟和其他灭绝的鸟类铺平了道路</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/de-extinction-company-says-it-hatched-chicks-from-artificial-eggs-paving-the-way-for-resurrecting-dodos-and-other-bygone-birds-180988766/</link><description>Colossal Biosciences 宣布 3D 打印的蜂窝结构中诞生了 26 只活的小鸡。但该公司不打算在论文中详细介绍该系统，其使命也面临批评</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 20:09:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/de-extinction-company-says-it-hatched-chicks-from-artificial-eggs-paving-the-way-for-resurrecting-dodos-and-other-bygone-birds-180988766/</guid></item><item><title>为什么这位古罗马士兵的墓碑隐藏在路易斯安那州的后院？考古学家解开了这个谜团，并帮助将文物送回意大利</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-was-this-ancient-roman-soldiers-gravestone-hidden-in-a-louisiana-backyard-archaeologists-solved-the-mystery-and-helped-return-the-artifact-to-italy-180988761/</link><description>去年在新奥尔良一处房产上出现的墓碑曾经属于一名去世于近 2000 年前的罗马士兵。官员们最近在罗马举行的仪式上归还了这块石头</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 18:30:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-was-this-ancient-roman-soldiers-gravestone-hidden-in-a-louisiana-backyard-archaeologists-solved-the-mystery-and-helped-return-the-artifact-to-italy-180988761/</guid></item><item><title>《蒙娜丽莎》要搬到新家了。卢浮宫刚刚宣布了将设计她的私人套房的建筑师</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mona-lisa-is-moving-to-a-new-home-the-louvre-just-announced-the-architects-who-will-design-her-private-suite-180988763/</link><description>游客无需参观卢浮宫的其他部分即可欣赏达芬奇的杰作，博物馆的游客流量每年将增长 300 万人次</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 18:27:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mona-lisa-is-moving-to-a-new-home-the-louvre-just-announced-the-architects-who-will-design-her-private-suite-180988763/</guid></item></channel></rss>